Between Two Waters - Seychelles Pavilion

PLANE—SITE / Vimeo
PLANE-SITE: plane-site.com The Republic of Seychelles announce their first contribution to the 15th International Architecture Exhibition, La Biennale di Venezia (28 May-27 November 2016), with an exhibition titled Between Two Waters, Searching for Expression in the Seychelles. Located in Palazzo Michiel and facing the Grand Canal, the Pavilion of the Seychelles transports visitors to the 115-island archipelago-the least populated nation in Africa.

The City of the Future Is Already Here

The Atlantic / Vimeo
In central Arizona there exists an experimental town called Arcosanti. It's built on the principles of arcology, which combines architecture and ecology to envision a city that works in tandem with the Earth's resources. In this short documentary, The Atlantic goes inside this distinctive urban space to understand how Arcosanti plans to reconstruct how humans envision cities.
